    "Tennessee Governor Bill Haslam was the president of his family's chain of truck stops, Pilot Flying J, for four years until 1999.",
    "Bill's father bought a gas station in Virginia in 1958 and founded Pilot Flying J, which now operates in more than 900 locations in North America.",
    "Berkshire Hathaway paid a reported $2.8 billion for 39% of Pilot in 2017 and will acquire another 41% by 2023.",
    "Haslam was elected the mayor of Knoxville in 2003 and became governor in 2010. He left office in 2019.",
    "Pilot has more than 750 locations in 44 states and hit $29 billion in revenue in 2018."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Pilot admitted to defrauding its customers in a $92 million settlement with the DOJ in July 2014.",
    "Bill told the magazine at Emory College, his alma mater, that when he was an undergraduate, he thought there was no way he would go into politics."
